Mammals are not directly descended from true reptiles as it is understood in a phylogenetic sense. The clade that includes class Reptilia, Sauropsida, is a sister taxon to Synapsida which include mammals.
All land vertebrates are Tetrapods, and although early tetrapods lived an amphibious lifestyle they aren't amphibians as in a member of the class Amphibia.
Birds however are literally reptiles, they are genetically in the class.

Author here. The way I think of it is that the MC is dealing as much with his own mental state and the changes in his life as he's dealing with the changes of the world as a whole. He both wants and doesn't want to know, since the information could add to the mental load he's already carrying. As such, he's going for the most important questions first (Is Earth still around? Is humanity still a thing?) before he starts dealing with why humans around him seem to care more about beasts than other humans. He's not badly off, after all, and is probably acting the same way with Emily as most other humans are acting around their respective owners. I think I do struggle with getting some of this across, because I didn't have a proper plan in place when I started, and retroactively explaining how a character felt a chapter ago is really awkward. I'm hoping I can improve on this as I go along, and maybe I can revise some of the worst shortcomings after I've completed the story
